label: A2B3_tP20_102_2c_b2c-001
title: Gd$_{3}$Al$_{2}$ Structure
comments:
We have added the reference to (Baenziger, 1964), which has the description of this structure. 
 Space group $P4_{2}nm$ \#102 allows an arbitary placement of the origin of the $z$-axis.  We choose this so that $z_{1} = 1/2$ for the Gd-I atom. This represents a shift of $0.017 c$ from the origin of (Baenziger, 1964). 
 (Buschow, 1965) says that the prototype for this structure is Zr$_{3}$Al$_{2}$, but note that there is a competing Zr$_{3}$Al$_{2}$ structure in \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_tP20_136_j_dfg-001}{in the centrosymmetric space group $P4_{2}/mnm$ \#136}.
